==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: promotion
<hw>pro*mo"tion</hw> <pr>(pr⟦osl⟧*m⟦omac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>promotio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>promotion</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The act of promoting, advancing, or encouraging; the act of
exalting in rank or honor; also, the condition of being advanced,
encouraged, or exalted in honor; preferment.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Promotion</qex> cometh neither from the east, nor from the
west, nor from the south.</q> <rj><qau>Ps. lxxv. 6.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Promotive</ent>⟦br⟧
